                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Ostracon, section (three fragments joined) of the rim of a buff-coloured pottery dish, shallow with slightly flaring sides and turned rim, the fabric is relatively fine, covered with a burnished cream-orange slip, with remains of two columns of Coptic text written in black ink, separated by drawn lines, on the interior, the first column comprises nine and the second eight lines of text, containing multiplication tables.</note>
                     <note type="general">Writing on the interior.</note>
